main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a star-like bright white light in the sky that appeared to have flickering red and green lights.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 10 minutes, moving slowly from the southwest to the west and slightly up and down.
The observer, a 45-50 year old housewife, was at her home looking out a window facing west when she saw the object.
The weather conditions at the time were clear with a moonlit night and good visibility.
The investigating officer suggested the object could have been the planet Venus, and the up and down movement could have been caused by atmospheric effects.
No photographs or physical evidence of the object were available.
sighted object: a star-like bright white light with flickering red and green lights
witnesses: 1 civilian observer, a 45-50 year old housewife
